  "name": "Venous Thromboembolism - Anticoagulant Medication Query",
  "description": "Tests ability to find VTE patients via anticoagulant medications. VTE treatment includes warfarin (vitamin K antagonist), DOACs (apixaban, rivaroxaban, dabigatran), and parenteral enoxaparin (LMWH). All have heavy cross-indication with atrial fibrillation, mechanical valves, and post-op prophylaxis — so meds alone don't equal VTE. The Synthea module distributes patients across these classes.",
  "prompt": "Find patients prescribed anticoagulant medications used to treat venous thromboembolism, including warfarin, apixaban, rivaroxaban, dabigatran, and enoxaparin.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients on blood thinners.",
    "broad": "Find patients prescribed therapeutic anticoagulants used for venous thromboembolism — vitamin K antagonists (warfarin), direct oral anticoagulants or DOACs (apixaban, rivaroxaban, dabigatran), and low-molecular-weight heparin (enoxaparin).",
    "expert": "I need MedicationRequest resources for any therapeutic anticoagulant. Use these RxNorm ingredient codes: 11289 (warfarin, vitamin K antagonist), 1364430 (apixaban, factor Xa inhibitor), 1114195 (rivaroxaban, factor Xa inhibitor), 1037042 (dabigatran etexilate, direct thrombin inhibitor), 67108 (enoxaparin, LMWH). Combine in a single comma-separated code search. Note all have heavy cross-indication use — warfarin/DOACs for AFib stroke prevention, enoxaparin for post-op DVT prophylaxis."
  },
